<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Sampling Rate" class="currentChild" href="Sampling_Rate">Sampling Rate</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In the digitizing of images, sounds, and video, the <a title="Frequency" href="Frequency">frequency</a> with which points are recorded. 
</p>
<p id="l3">
In <a title="Scanning" href="Scanning">scanning</a>, the sampling rate is measured as the number of samples taken per inch (or millimeter), both horizontally and vertically. Operator-controlled variations of the sampling rate include the <a title="Pixel" href="Pixel">pixel</a> size to be sampled, and the <a title="Resolution" href="Resolution">resolution</a> at which the image is to be sampled. Also referred to as the <a title="Sampling Frequency" href="Sampling_Frequency">sampling frequency</a>. 
</p>
